{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:08:47.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 327, "tokens_out": 467, "elapsed_ms": 22193, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a fully functional landing page for a fictional productivity app called \"Flowdesk\". Deliver everything in a single file: index.html. The file must include all CSS in a <style> tag and all JavaScript in a <script> tag — no external files, no CDN links.\n\nThe page must include:\n- A navbar with logo text and 3 navigation links\n- A hero section with headline, subheading, and a CTA button\n- A features section with 3 cards (icon, title, description)\n- A footer with copyright text\n\nRequirements: fully responsive (mobile + desktop), semantic HTML5, smooth scroll on nav links, hover states on the CTA and cards. Deliver index.html to the workspace.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T00:10:19.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1378, "tokens_out": 875, "elapsed_ms": 92120, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"setup-html-structure\",\n      \"description\": \"Create index.html with full HTML5 document structure, including <html>, <head>, <body>, and semantic tags (header, main, section, footer). Include a <style> tag in the head and a <script> tag before the closing body tag. Set up the viewport meta tag for responsiveness.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"implement-navbar\",\n      \"description\": \"Build a responsive navigation bar in index.html with logo text 'Flowdesk' on the left and three navigation links ('Features', 'Pricing', 'Contact') on the right. Ensure smooth scrolling to sections when links are clicked using inline JavaScript in the <script> tag.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"design-hero-section\",\n      \"description\": \"Create a hero section in index.html with a compelling headline 'Get More Done with Flowdesk', a subheading 'The all-in-one workspace for teams who value focus and speed', and a CTA button 'Start Free Trial'. Style with CSS in the <style> tag to be responsive and include a hover effect on the button.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"build-features-section\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement a features section in index.html with three feature cards arranged in a responsive grid. Each card must include an icon (using Unicode or emoji), a title (e.g., 'Task Management', 'Time Tracking', 'Team Collaboration'), and a short description. Add hover effects using CSS in the <style> tag.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"create-footer\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a footer to index.html with centered copyright text: '\\u00a9 2024 Flowdesk. All rights reserved.' Style with CSS to remain at the bottom and be responsive across devices.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"ensure-responsiveness\",\n      \"description\": \"Refine CSS in the <style> tag to ensure full responsiveness: mobile-first layout, flexbox or grid for alignment, media queries for desktop view, and accessible navigation (collapsible menu on mobile if needed). Test smooth scroll behavior and hover states across screen sizes.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
